40th Street, south side, from No. 252 (?) east of Eighth Avenue to No. 200 at Seventh Avenue. No. 250 is a new fourteen-story loft building for the garment trade. No. 246-240, adjoining it, is the Printing Press Building, which was built since 1920 on the site of the Abyssinian Baptist Church. About 1924.
Edwin Levick, Photographer.
